  "id": "0a46c4534f2d35d3",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/docker/6fb0d713-acd2-4a0e-8d99-a30e9e23e780/application",
    "company": "Docker",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "0a46c4534f2d35d3",
    "department": "Sales",
    "description": "At Docker, we make app development easier so developers can focus on what matters. Our remote-first team spans the globe, united by a passion for innovation and great developer experiences. With over 20 million monthly users and 20 billion image pulls, Docker is the #1 tool for building, sharing, and running apps—trusted by startups and Fortune 100s alike. We’re growing fast and just getting started. Come join us for a whale of a ride!\n\nDocker is looking for a talented Senior Partner Solutions Engineer (PSE) to join our growing team focused on strategic partnerships. In this high-impact role, you will work closely with Independent Software Vendors (ISVs), Cloud Service Providers (CSPs), Systems Integrators (SIs), and Value-Added Resellers (VARs) to drive adoption and integration of Docker technologies across our partner ecosystem. You will play a pivotal role in enabling partners at both scale and depth, supporting joint go-to-market (GTM) motions, and guiding integration and delivery of Docker’s products and solutions. This position reports to the Sr. Director of Solutions Engineering and works closely with the Partner Sales Team, Field SEs, Technical Alliances, and Enablement teams.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\nPartner Engagement \u0026 Enablement\n\n - Design and deliver scalable enablement programs, including technical learning paths and certifications (e.g., via MindTickle or similar platforms).\n\n - Conduct 1:1 technical enablement for strategic partners (e.g., workshops, roadmap sessions, technical deep-dives, speaking engagements).\n\n - Serve as the technical advisor for partners integrating Docker into their service offerings or product stacks.\n\nJoint Go-To-Market Support\n\n - Collaborate with partner and Docker sales teams to drive joint account planning and co-selling opportunities.\n\n - Support product positioning and technical validation during joint sales engagements.\n\n - Guide “sell-with” and “sell-through” partner models with clarity on what’s GA and ready for delivery (“what’s on the truck”).\n\nTechnical Alliances \u0026 Product Alignment\n\n - Collaborate with Product and Engineering teams on roadmap alignment, beta/EAP program participation, and technical integrations with CSPs and ISVs.\n\n - Advocate for partner-driven feature requests and co-building initiatives back to the Docker product team.\n\nField and Regional Collaboration\n\n - Partner with regional Field SEs to ensure alignment with market-specific requirements and vertical priorities for NA (e.g., FedGov, SLED).\n\n - Represent regional partner technical needs and priorities in internal planning discussions.\n\nContent Creation \u0026 Technical Leadership\n\n - Author and maintain reusable technical content such as integration guides, architectural diagrams, and enablement videos tailored for partners.\n\n - Represent Docker at partner events, conferences, and webinars as a technical expert and evangelist.\n   \n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 7+ years of experience in solutions engineering, partner engineering, or similar technical roles, with proven experience in a partner-facing or channel SE capacity at a developer tools, DevOps, DevSecOps, or cloud infrastructure company.\n\n - Deep technical understanding of Docker, containers, and modern CI/CD and DevSecOps practices.\n\n - Familiarity with application security principles and securing the software supply chain, including SBOMs, image scanning, and secure delivery pipelines.\n\n - Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP), infrastructure technologies, and security best practices.\n\n - Strong ability to communicate technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.\n\n - Skilled in building scalable enablement content and delivering 1:1 and 1-to-many technical education.\n\n - Experience working with cross-functional teams, including sales, product, and engineering.\n\n - Willingness to travel to partner sites and events (~30% expected).\n   \n\n\nWHAT TO EXPECT\n\n\nFIRST 30 DAYS\n\n - Participate in onboarding with a focus on Docker product knowledge and partner strategy.\n\n - Learn tooling and internal systems (Salesforce, Looker, Docker platform) and connect with internal stakeholders.\n\n - Begin shadowing partner calls and reviewing existing enablement materials.\n   \n\n\n60 DAYS\n\n - Lead enablement sessions for selected regional partners.\n\n - Begin supporting joint-account planning and identifying co-sell opportunities.\n\n - Collaborate with Technical Alliances on roadmap integration discussions.\n   \n\n\n90 DAYS\n\n - Deliver partner workshops independently.\n\n - Produce partner-facing technical content.\n\nOwn the technical strategy for one or more partner segments (ISVs, CSPs, etc.).\n\n\nDocker does not offer visa sponsorship for this role.\n\nWe use Covey as part of our hiring and / or promotional process for jobs in NYC and certain features may qualify it as an AEDT. As part of the evaluation process we provide Covey with job requirements and candidate submitted applications. We began using Covey Scout for Inbound https://getcovey.com/product/covey-scout-inbound on April 13, 2024.\n\nPlease see the independent bias audit report covering our use of Covey here https://getcovey.com/nyc-local-law-144.\n\nPerks\n\n - Freedom \u0026 flexibility; fit your work around your life\n\n - Designated quarterly Whaleness Days plus end of year Whaleness break\n\n - Home office setup; we want you comfortable while you work\n\n - 16 weeks of paid Parental leave\n\n - Technology stipend equivalent to $100 net/month\n\n - PTO plan that encourages you to take time to do the things you enjoy\n\n - Training stipend for conferences, courses and classes\n\n - Equity; we are a growing start-up and want all employees to have a share in the success of the company\n\n - Docker Swag\n\n - Medical benefits, retirement and holidays vary by country\n\n - Remote-first culture, with offices in Seattle and Paris\n\nDocker embraces diversity and equal opportunity. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. The more inclusive we are, the better our company will be.\n\n#LI-REMOTE",
